# HotelAI Coding Standards

`docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md` is the source of truth for TypeScript, React, imports, exports, Server/Client boundaries, error handling, forms, validation, linting, env, and git hygiene.

Keep this rule short. Do not copy coding standards here.

## Non-Negotiables

- `strict` TypeScript, no `any`, no TypeScript `enum`.
- Named exports for components/functions; default exports only for Next route pages.
- `import type` for type-only imports.
- User-facing messages are Russian.
- Never commit `.env`, secrets, zip artifacts, or generated build output.
